<h2>
	<span class="t-type">Cours, TD et TP</span> 
	<span class="t-title"> Lani&egrave;re SCAN - Groupe 71 </span>
	<span class="t-year">(PC - 2&egrave;me ann&eacute;e)</span> 
</h2>
	Algorithmics and the Pascal programming language:
	<ul>
		<li>Input/output</li>
		<li>Pointers</li>
    	<li>Object oriented programming</li>
     	<li>User interface design: event based programming</li>
		<li>Dynamic data structures: lists, trees, graphs</li>
		<li>Mini projet </li>
	</ul>

	<h3>Mini-projects</h3>
	
	Example codes and tutorials:
	<ul>
		<li> Animation, multiple moving objects managed by a class hierarchy and virtual "move()" functions. User interactin: 
			 <a href="pc-miniprojects/tutorials/tutorial_cwolf_flying_sheep.zip">[ZIP]</a></li>		
		<li>How to move graphics with the mouse (possible large animataions!) - paint directly on the canvas of the form
			 <a href="pc-miniprojects/tutorials/mousemove_onformdirect.tgz">[TAR-GZ]</a></li>		
		<li>How to use TStringGrids, and do a (small!) animation with a timage, and how to use timers
			<a href="pc-miniprojects/tutorials/tutorial.tgz">[TAR-GZ]</a></li>
		<li>How to stretch an image <a href="pc-miniprojects/tutorials/tutorial_stretch.tgz">[TAR-GZ]</a></li>
		<li>How to use a color dialog<a href="pc-miniprojects/tutorials/tutorial_tcolordialog.tgz">[TAR-GZ]</a></li>
	</ul>

